  <!--   Chapter  4   -->
  <!--   **********   -->
  <chapter number="4" style="c" sid="REV 4" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="REV 4:1" />After all of this I looked, and—just like that—a door up in the sky had been opened, and the first voice
        I heard was speaking to me like a trumpet <char style="it">does when sounding an alert</char>, saying,
        “Come up here and I’ll show you what must come to pass after these things.” <verse eid="REV 4:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="REV 4:2" />Immediately I wound up in <char style="it">the</char> Spirit and—just like that—a throne was situated
        there in the sky, and someone was sitting on the throne, <verse eid="REV 4:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="REV 4:3" />and the one sitting looked like <char style="it">he was made of</char> stone, of jasper and sardius,
        and a rainbow that looked just like emerald went around the throne. <verse eid="REV 4:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="REV 4:4" />And twenty-four <char style="it">smaller </char>thrones surrounded the <char style="it">one </char>throne,
        and upon the <char style="it">smaller </char>thrones were seated twenty-four elders<char style="sup">[A]</char>
        dressed in white and upon their heads were golden laurels, victors’ crowns. <verse eid="REV 4:4" />
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="REV 4:5" />Out of the <char style="it">one</char> throne came thunder and lightning. Seven lamps of fire burned
        before the throne, and these are the seven Spirits of God. <verse eid="REV 4:5" />
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="REV 4:6" />And before the throne there was a glass lake like crystal.
    </para>
    <para style="p" vid="REV 4:6">In the midst of the throne and around the throne were four animal-like creatures, with eyes all over
        them on the front and on the back. <verse eid="REV 4:6"/>
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="REV 4:7" />The first creature was like a lion, the second like a calf, the third had the face of a man, the fourth
        was like a flying eagle. <verse eid="REV 4:7" />
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="REV 4:8" />And each one of the four creatures had six wings, and they were full of eyes around them and inside of
        them. Day and night they never stopped saying,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 4:8"></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 4:8">Holy, holy, holy</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 4:8">Lord God Almighty</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 4:8">Who was, Who is, Who’s coming<verse eid="REV 4:8"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="REV 4:9" />And when the creatures give glory, honor, and thanksgiving to the One seated on the throne, to the One
        who lives forever and ever, <verse eid="REV 4:9" />
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="REV 4:10" />the twenty-four elders fall <char style="it">and prostrate themselves </char>before the One sitting on
        the throne and worship the One who lives forever and ever, and toss their wreaths before the throne saying,<verse eid="REV 4:10" />
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="pi">
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="REV 4:11" />You are worthy, our Lord God
    </para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 4:11">To receive the glory, the honor, and the power</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 4:11">Because You created all things</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 4:11">And by means of Your will</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 4:11">They were <char style="it">determined to be </char>and were created<verse eid="REV 4:11"/>
    </para>
  <!--   .........   -->
  <!--   Footnotes   -->
  <!--   .........   -->
    <note caller="[A]" style="f">
      <char style="fk">[A]</char>
      <char style="ft"><char style="it">elders</char>…In the time of Jesus and for years prior to that, Israel had a national
        tribunal of judges known as the Sanhedrin over all of Israel, and there were lesser such tribunals that
        ruled over each city. This pattern of having a tribunal board is replicated in John’s vision.</char>
    </note>
  <chapter eid="REV 4" />
  <!--   **********   -->
  <!--   Chapter  5   -->
  <!--   **********   -->
  <chapter number="5" style="c" sid="REV 5" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="REV 5:1" />And I saw a scroll in the right hand of the of the One sitting on the throne, and the scroll <char style="it">was
        full of writing </char>on both the front and back sides and was sealed <char style="it">shut</char><char
        style="sup">[A]</char><char style="it"> </char>with seven seals. <verse eid="REV 5:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="REV 5:2" />I saw a powerful angel proclaiming in a loud voice, “Who’s worthy to break the seals and open the scroll<char
        style="sup">[B]</char>?” <verse eid="REV 5:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="REV 5:3" />They kept trying to find someone who was able to, and they couldn’t find anyone in heaven, on the earth,
        nor in the underworld <char style="it">of death</char><char style="sup">[a]</char><char style="it"> </char>to
        open the scroll or to <char style="it">even</char> look at it. <verse eid="REV 5:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="REV 5:4" />They proceeded to weep intensely since nobody was found worthy enough to open the scroll or to <char
        style="it">even </char>look at it. <verse eid="REV 5:4" />
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="REV 5:5" />But one of the elders <char style="it">then </char>tells me, “Don’t cry. Look here—the lion of the tribe
        of Judah, <char style="it">from </char>the shoot<char style="sup">[b]</char> of David, has prevailed
        <char style="it">in earning the right</char> to break the seven seals and open the scroll.”<verse eid="REV 5:5" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="REV 5:6" />In the midst of the throne and the four creatures and in the midst of the elders, I saw a lamb standing
        there looking as though he had been slain, having seven horns seven eyes, which are the Seven Spirits
        of God which have been sent out all over the planet. <verse eid="REV 5:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="REV 5:7" />He came and took what was in the right hand of the One sitting on the throne, <verse eid="REV 5:7" />
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="REV 5:8" />and when he took the scroll, the four creatures and the twenty-four elders fell <char style="it">and
        prostrated themselves </char>before the lamb, each of them having a harp and a golden vial of incense,
        which are the prayers of those who are holy<char style="sup">[c]</char>. <verse eid="REV 5:8" />
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="REV 5:9" />And they sing a new song saying <char style="it">in it</char>,
    </para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 5:9"></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 5:9">You are worthy to take the scroll</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 5:9">And to break open its seals</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 5:9">Because you were slain and with your blood</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 5:9">Purchased for God those</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 5:9">From among every clan<char style="sup">[d]</char>, language, culture<char style="sup">[e]</char>, and
        ethnicity.<verse eid="REV 5:9"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi">
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="REV 5:10" />And you made them into a priestly kingdom<char style="sup">[f]</char> for our God,
    </para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 5:10">And they will reign upon the earth.<verse eid="REV 5:10"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="REV 5:11" />I looked and heard a sound of many angels surrounding the throne and of the creatures and elders. There
        were millions and millions and billions and billions<char style="sup">[C]</char> in number, <verse eid="REV 5:11" />
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="REV 5:12" />all saying in a loud voice,
    </para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 5:12"></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 5:12">Worthy is the slain lamb to receive</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 5:12">The power and wealth and wisdom and strength</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 5:12">And honor and glory and thanksgiving <char style="it">due him</char><verse eid="REV 5:12"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="m">
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="REV 5:13" />I heard all of creation that’s in the sky, on the earth, below the earth, on top of the sea, and beneath
        the sea saying,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 5:13"></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 5:13">To the One sitting upon the throne and to the lamb</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 5:13"><char style="it">Be </char>the thanksgiving, honor, glory, might</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 5:13">Forever and ever<verse eid="REV 5:13"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="m">
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="REV 5:14" />The four creatures proceeded to say, “So be it<char style="sup">[g]</char>,” and the elders fell <char
        style="it">and prostrated themselves </char>and offered up worship.<verse eid="REV 5:14" />
    </para>
