  <chapter number="12" style="c" sid="REV 12" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="REV 12:1" />A great portent was seen in heaven: a woman clothed in the sun<char style="sup">[a]</char>, the moon
        under her feet, a crown with twelve stars on her head, <verse eid="REV 12:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="REV 12:2" />and with a baby in her womb, screaming because of labor pains, the agony of giving birth. <verse eid="REV 12:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="REV 12:3" />I saw another portent in heaven, and—out of nowhere—a huge red dragon with seven heads and ten horns
        and with ornamental headbands<char style="sup">[b]</char> on his head. <verse eid="REV 12:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="REV 12:4" />His tail swept a third of the stars, dragging them <char style="it">until he’d completely gotten ahold
        of them</char><char style="sup">[A]</char>, and flung them to the Earth.</para>
    <para style="p" vid="REV 12:4">The dragon stood before the woman who was about to give birth, so that he could devour the child when
        she gives birth. <verse eid="REV 12:4"/>
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="REV 12:5" />She gave birth to a son—a male<char style="it">-child</char>—who would <char style="it">some day </char>shepherd
        (rule) every nation with an iron staff<char style="sup">[B]</char>. Her child was snatched away from
        her <char style="it">and taken </char>to God and to His throne. <verse eid="REV 12:5" />
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="REV 12:6" />The woman fled to the backcountry, where nobody was around, where, <char style="it">by God’s direction</char>,
        a place in it had been prepared for her, so that she would be taken care of<char style="sup">[c]</char>
        for 1260 days, allowing her to recuperate.<verse eid="REV 12:6" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="REV 12:7" />A war occurred in heaven: Michael and his angels waged war with the dragon, and the dragon and his angels
        waged war <char style="it">against him. </char><verse eid="REV 12:7" />
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="REV 12:8" />But he was not powerful enough, nor could he establish a foothold in heaven<char style="sup">[d]</char>,<verse eid="REV 12:8" />
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="REV 12:9" />and the Great Dragon, the Ancient Serpent, the one called “Slanderer” (i.e. “the Devil”)—yes indeed:
        Satan—the one who deceives the entire inhabited world—he was driven to the Earth, and his angels too
        were driven out with him. <verse eid="REV 12:9" />
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="REV 12:10" />I heard a loud voice in heaven saying,
    </para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 12:10"></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 12:10">The end of our misery<char style="sup">[e]</char>, the security, the power,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 12:10">The kingdom of our God,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 12:10">And the authority of His Messiah, His Christ</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 12:10">Starts right now,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 12:10">Since our comrades’<char style="sup">[f]</char> accuser has been driven <char style="it">out,</char></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 12:10">The one who accuses them before our God day and night.<verse eid="REV 12:10"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi">
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="REV 12:11" />And they defeated him by means of the lamb’s blood
    </para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 12:11">And the logic of his solemn declaration<char style="sup">[g]</char>.</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 12:11">They didn’t love their life</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 12:11"><char style="it">Even </char>to the point of death.<verse eid="REV 12:11"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi">
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="REV 12:12" />On account of this be glad:
    </para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 12:12"><char style="it">You </char>the sky, the atmosphere, outer space, and heaven</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 12:12">And those who are camped out<char style="sup">[h]</char> in you—</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 12:12">Woe to the land and sea</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 12:12">Because the devil’s <char style="it">headed</char> your way filled with rage,</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="REV 12:12">Knowing that he has <char style="it">only </char>a small window of time <char style="it">left</char>.<verse eid="REV 12:12"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="REV 12:13" />And when the dragon saw that he was driven to the Earth, he pursued the woman who gave birth to the man-child.<verse eid="REV 12:13" />
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="REV 12:14" />The woman was given a pair of giant vulture<char style="sup">[i]</char> wings, so that she could fly
        to the place set aside for her in the backcountry, where she is taken care of three-and-a-half years<char
        style="sup">[j]</char>, kept away from the serpent’s single-minded focus<char style="sup">[k]</char>.<verse eid="REV 12:14" />
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="REV 12:15" />The serpent spewed water like a river from his mouth, going after the woman by making a torrent that
        would sweep her away; <verse eid="REV 12:15" />
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="REV 12:16" />but the land came to the woman’s aid: the ground opened its mouth and drank the river up which the dragon
        spewed out of his mouth. <verse eid="REV 12:16" />
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="REV 12:17" />The dragon became furious with the woman and went off to wage war with the remainder of her offspring,
        those who keep God’s commandments and who have something to attest to as far as Jesus is concerned<char
        style="sup">[l]</char>.<verse eid="REV 12:17" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="18" style="v" sid="REV 12:18" />And <char style="it">the dragon</char> stood on the seashore<char style="sup">[C]</char>…<verse eid="REV 12:18" />
    </para>
