        <char style="it">drags a third of the stars</char>. Note the present tense <char style="it">drags </char>in
        the GT. Although <char style="it">drags </char>is present tense in form, it is past tense in meaning;
        this is a figure of speech. The interpolation <char style="it">until he’d completely gotten ahold of
        them </char>reflects the additional meaning that the figure of speech is communicating. Ref. note of
        John 1:5.</char>
